# Next.js App Router — MyConciergeHotel.com

## Rendering strategy

- Default to **Server Components**. Add `'use client'` only when you genuinely need state, effects, refs, or browser APIs.
- For pages that don't need per-request data, prefer **ISR** with `export const revalidate = N` over `force-dynamic`.
- `force-dynamic` is acceptable when a shared layout reads `cookies()`/`headers()` (e.g. auth area in header) — but see [ADR-0007](../../docs/adr/0007-isr-via-auth-client-island.md) for the auth client island pattern that re-enables ISR.
- `generateStaticParams` must defensively return `[]` if upstream data is unavailable — never throw during build.

## Hotel detail + room sub-pages (CDC §2 + ADR-0008/0009)

- **Hotel detail** lives at `app/[locale]/hotel/[slug]/page.tsx` with **`export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`** — **permanent and justified** by the per-request CSP nonce read via `headers()` (hard rule `security-csp.mdc`). Per **[ADR-0027](../../docs/adr/0027-csp-model-evolution.md) (CSP-α)** the ISR runtime target is **dropped** on nonce-bearing pages and the nonce → hash migration is **not** pursued; **[ADR-0026](../../docs/adr/0026-csp-rendering-strategy.md) is Rejected**. No CDN `s-maxage` on the HTML document (a frozen nonce reopens PR #57). [ADR-0007](../../docs/adr/0007-isr-via-auth-client-island.md) is amended accordingly. The "editorial-fiche-first" decision (no live booking / `Offer` before Phase 6) is [ADR-0025](../../docs/adr/0025-booking-integration-last-brick.md) — **not** ADR-0024 (photos).
- **Room sub-pages** live at `app/[locale]/hotel/[slug]/chambres/[roomSlug]/page.tsx`:
  - Same rendering as the parent: **`force-dynamic` permanent** (per-request CSP nonce, ADR-0027 CSP-α). ISR runtime is not pursued on nonce-bearing pages.
  - `generateStaticParams` should perform a **single shared Supabase fetch** that returns both parent slugs and their room slugs, returned as a flat array of `{ slug, roomSlug }` — avoids the N+1 pattern.
  - `generateMetadata` is localised, `alternates.canonical` = `/hotel/[slug]/chambres/[roomSlug]` (**never** the parent), `alternates.languages` mirrors V1 locales.
  - If the room has < 5 photos or < 200 words description, return `{ robots: { index: false, follow: false } }` (room remains visible to humans but not indexed until the editor completes it).
  - JSON-LD: emit `HotelRoom` (or `Room`) + `Offer` + `BreadcrumbList` + `ImageObject[]` + `isPartOf` referencing the parent hotel `@id`.
- Both pages share the breadcrumb shape: `Accueil > Destination > [Ville] > [Hotel] > [Chambre]`.

## Metadata & SEO

- Every page exports `generateMetadata`. Localised `title`/`description` come from `next-intl`.
- Set `alternates.canonical` + `alternates.languages` (fr-FR, en, x-default).
- 404-able pages (`getXyz === null`) must return `{ robots: { index: false, follow: false } }`.
- Use `JsonLdScript` from `@/components/seo/json-ld` for every JSON-LD payload (it reads the CSP nonce). Never inline `<script>` directly.

## Server Actions / Route Handlers

- Validate input with **Zod** at the boundary. Reject with a discriminated `Result` union.
- Never let a domain error bubble as a stack trace. Map to user-friendly i18n keys.
- Use idempotency keys (`request-id` cookie or `Idempotency-Key` header) on booking-side actions.

## Middleware

- `apps/web/src/middleware.ts` is the single source of truth for: locale routing, Supabase session refresh, CSP nonce.
- The nonce is propagated via `request.headers.set('x-nonce', …)` so Server Components can read it.
- Don't add headers in `next.config.ts`; consolidate them in middleware so they survive ISR.

## Data fetching

- Server Components fetch directly (no `useEffect`). Wrap with `unstable_cache` only when a vendor call is genuinely shared across routes.
- Tag fetches with `next: { tags: ['hotel:<id>'] }` so editors can `revalidateTag` from Payload hooks.
- Always handle the "env not configured" case (Supabase, Algolia, Redis) — fall back gracefully so dev / preview environments don't 500.

## i18n

- Use `next-intl` translations. **Never** hard-code French/English strings in `.tsx`.
- Plural / dynamic keys go in `messages/{fr,en}.json`. Keep keys parallel; missing-translation tests run in CI.

## Folder layout

```
apps/web/src/
  app/[locale]/...   # localised public routes
  app/.well-known/   # agent-skills.json, etc.
  app/sitemap.xml/   # route handlers (force-static)
  components/        # shared client + server components
  server/            # server-only helpers (Supabase queries, batch fetchers)
  lib/               # framework-agnostic helpers (csp, env, utils)
  i18n/              # routing, navigation, messages
```

See `.cursor/skills/nextjs-app-router/SKILL.md` for deeper guidance on the folder layout.
